OL,3,CLondon's roads worst in Europe for
OL,4,Ctraffic and delays
OL,6,FBristol was the second worst UK city
OL,7,Ffor traffic, with 65 hours of delays
OL,8,Fper driver, ahead of Leeds in third
OL,9,Fspot (60 hours).
OL,11,FManchester was in fourth position
OL,12,Fafter a 13% year-on-year rise in
OL,13,Fdelays, from 54 hours to 61 hours.
OL,15,FThe ranking is based on the length of
OL,16,Fdelays, weighted by the size of each
OL,17,Fcity's population.
